Reality tv stars are known to have to push their energy and personalities to the limit to get famous. So what happens when these celebs are children? In the case of the hit show Toddlers and Tiaras, we are shown a wide variety of kids who are being groomed not only for beauty pageants, but for the camera as well. Parents on these shows can make the worst decisions ever. Itâ€™s a competition for sure, not only for first place but also for the cameras attention. Some moms will do anything to win the contest, whether itâ€™s modifying the childâ€™s clothing in extreme ways, or changing the girlâ€™s body to suit the needs of the competition. Beauty pageants are kill or be killed for these moms, and they pull out all the stops. Some moms even feed strange substances to their children to make them perform better. Is red bull OK to give to a kid? Probably not. But that doesnâ€™t stop one of these mothers from doing it anyways! And viewers at home are affected too. Some of these moms make their kids do things on the catwalk or on stage that can influence children watching at home. Would you want your child to see adult activities being performed by kids, making them seem cool to do? We sure hope not! Well, stand back if you arenâ€™t ready for this beauty pageant: here comes Honey Boo Boo! Here are the ten worst parents of Toddlers and Tiaras.

The news was confirmed by Posey's mother on Monday, May 2, 2022, who asked for privacy for her family during this trying time. title: 'Toddlers and Tiaras' star Kailia Posey left behind a gift for her mom before she died by suicide
description: "Toddlers and Tiaras" star Kailia Posey left behind a note and a gift for her mother before she died by suicide.Posey's mother Marcy Gatterman opened up about the 16-year-old's final days in a recent interview with E! News.Â "The days and weeks leading up to this, it seemed fine to me," Gatterman told the outlet. "I didn't go through her phone. For prom, she went with a bunch of friends. And the  day, everything was fine."Â However, on May 1, Posey took a family car after her mother left to go to the store and never returned.  Â Â Her body was found on May 2 and the cause and manner of death was confirmed by the Whatcom County Medical Examiner's Office Wednesday in a release shared online.Â The 16-year-old pageant star died by "asphyxia due to ligature hanging and the manner is suicide," according to authorities.Â "She left a note for me and then one for her best friend," Gatterman revealed. "The note said that she loved me and that she was sorry and that her big brother is her best friend forever."  Â Â Posey had also ordered a blanket for her mother, which arrived two weeks after her death. The blanket was discovered by the pageant queen on TikTok and meant to be like a hug.Â "Dear Mom, even when I'm not  by, I want you to know I love and appreciate you. Always. Wrap yourself up in this and consider it a big hug. I love you," a note with the blanket said, according to Posey's mom.Â Gatterman also emphasized parents should be checking in on their children, and encouraged children to open up to their parents.Â "Parents who have teenagers, check their phones," she said. "And if you're struggling, talk to your parents. They're not judging you. They're going to get you the help that you need, but we need to know what you need in order get the help you need."  Â Â Posey got her start on "Toddlers and Tiaras," the same TLC show that launched the career of Alana "Honey Boo Boo" Thompson. The TLC show ran for seven seasons and ended in 2013. The show followed families as their young children competed in beauty pageants.
